Package com.stardevllc.stardata.api.interfaces.sql

Interface Column

All Superinterfaces:
Comparable<Column>
All Known Implementing Classes:
SQLColumn
public interface Column extends Comparable<Column>
This represents a column in a Table within a Database. Instances of this class are created for every field that is not ignored following the ignoring rules in the Table documentation
This class is mainly an internal class used by the library. You shouldn't need to interact with this class directly, however you can find how this works for how Columns work in this library
When determining the type of a field, this library first looks at the Codec and set it to a default of varchar(1000), this can be overridden with the Type annotation
It will then look at to see if there is a registered table in the database. if there is, then it set the values based on the primary key column of the table
Then it will look at the Type annotation for an override. Please note, these must be compatible.
For compatibility, it can just be default compatible, using a TypeHandler or ObjectCodec.
The name of the column can be taken from the name of the class, which will be all lower-case, or using the Name annotation.
You can use the other annotatations to customize the columns as you see fit. This library will not check to see if your configuration is wrong, you will get SQLExceptions if it is.
